comment: Very full and incredibly rich. This stuff used to be readily available, but the bourbon craze has left the supply dry. Such a shame because this was near the top of what a bourbon can be.

One to obsess over. Very smooth for the proof level. I get a little salt at the front end and a hint of smoke on the back end. A little sweeter than Blanton's, but not in a bad way. Likely a different barrel than the reviewer tasted. Need this in my collection.
proof  that you don't have to distil your own spirit to make amazing bourbon. this stuff is so round, so warm, toasty.
kept some for the future but wish i had more
This is the best burbon I have ever haf
Unfortunately, this whiskey is obscenely priced for it's quality. While it is a 5 star whiskey at $75 at the nearly $500 most people are chargning it is not.
